      <amcr:chranene_udaje>
        <amcr:lokalizace_okolnosti>Havlicek Street. Construction of homes on 8 plots in the historic part of the city.</amcr:lokalizace_okolnosti>
        <amcr:souhrn_upresneni>Eight plots in Havlíčkova Street (JV part of the historical core). Systematically examined 3 plots, remaining area probed with sections. Na ppč. 107/8 several objects (furnace, well, explosion pit, intruded object of indeterminate function) from the beginning of the 14th century. The site has been studied on 4 larger probes - surfaces (areas A, B, probes and, ß), as well as several smaller probes without naming them. Area A was spread over plot number 112. At the front of the lot, along the street line, layers and objects from the 14th-16th century were uncovered. In the interior of the parcel on the bedrock were layers of the 16th century. The profiles showed traces of the disastrous Beroun fires, dating back to 1544 and 1599. Area B was on lot 123. The walled object found on this lot was interpreted as a latrine. Construction activity starts in the 15th century and is especially intense from the 16th century. only aluminum comes from 14.s tol. A complex of 14th-century objects was found in the probe a and ß. A buried cellar with rows of fences, a well and a furnace (an extraordinary find in Czech archaeology). Two nameless probes examined the shallow, deep foundations of the wall. Another nameless probe on lots Nos. 114, 115 and 116 was an attempt to locate the supposed monastery garden, with no result. The thesis of the German half in this medieval city site also had no basis in the results of this research.</amcr:souhrn_upresneni>
      </amcr:chranene_udaje>
    </amcr:akce>
